maintainer delegate

```suggestion
/-- Build an isomorphism in the category `ProfiniteGrp` from
a `ContinuousMulEquiv` between `ProfiniteGrp`s. -/
```

```suggestion
instance isIso_toLimit (P : ProfiniteGrp.{u}) : IsIso (toLimit P) := by
```

```suggestion
    let i := asIso ((forgetâ‚‚ ProfiniteGrp Profinite).map f)
```
You should not explicitly refer to automatically generated universe variable names.

Why don't you use `(continuousMulEquivLimittoFiniteQuotientFunctor P).toProfiniteGrpIso` here? I suppose it does not really matter, because `continuousMulEquivLimittoFiniteQuotientFunctor` is also obtained from `Equiv.ofBijective`. But then at least the inverses of the category-theoretic spelling and the non-category-theoretic spelling agree definitionally.

I think I may need some suggestions from @kbuzzard  @faenuccio , as they suggested the adding of CategoryIso. Do we need the `ContinuousMulEquiv` and `Category.Iso` both or we only need the `Category.Iso`? If need both, I definitely should take the suggestion above. If we only need the `Category.Iso`, though there may be missing some API from `Category.Iso` to `ContinuousMulEquiv`, I can add it in this PR.
I believe we need both, because if someone is working with "true topological groups" instead of the corresponding object in `Profinite`, it would be more handy to have the `ContinuousMulEquiv`.
Thanks, the definition is fixed.
